  { :name => "Carnaval a Pedal 2012", :longitude => -70.6666667, :latitude => -33.45, :gmaps => true, :description => "Tres caravanas de ciclistas disfrazados o con bicis enchuladas que convergen en el centro de Santiago (Plaza Italia). \n\nEl ingenio popular chileno rodando por las calles de Santiago\n\nInscríbete | Disfrázate | Pedalea\n\nInscripciones oficiales en: http://carnavalapedal.com/", :start_time => "2012-12-15 09:30:00", :end_time => "2012-12-15 11:00:00", :address => "Echaurren 123-199, Santiago, Santiago Metropolitan Region, Chile", :fb_id => 283841978382617, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "https://fbcdn-profile-a.akamaihd.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/276642_283841978382617_1067456228_q.jpg", :atenders => 471, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-10-25 14:34:42", :updated_at => "2012-10-25 14:34:42" },
  { :name => "Estacionamientos Mysteryland", :longitude => -70.6512915, :latitude => -33.4457289, :gmaps => true, :description => "Estimados: No soy de hacer grupos para hacer reclamos, pero los cobros que esta haciendo la productor del Evento Mysteryland sobrepasan la billetera de cualquiera. Esta bien si la productora fija el precio de la entrada al doble que el año pasado, están en su derecho. Pero no comparto que nos obliguen a comprar un ticket de estacionamiento. Podrán decir, \"vallase en bus\", pero como ellos mismos mencionan, el bus te deja en el cruce con la carretera 5, y luego debes tomar otro busco, con costo, para llegar al recinto.\n\nSi la productora elige desarrollar un evento, a las afueras de Santiago, y no ofrece ningún sistema de transporte directo, mínimo nos deberían permitir el libre acceso en vehículo propios.\n\nSe que siendo 100 o 200 no lograremos nada, pero si nos juntamos todos los que asisten en auto, algo podremos lograr.\n\nGracias.\n\nCompartan el evento para saber que opinan todos", :start_time => "2012-12-14 01:00:00", :end_time => "2012-12-15 01:00:00", :address => "San Diego 50-80, Santiago, Santiago Metropolitan Region, Chile", :fb_id => 216262635165809, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "https://fbcdn-profile-a.akamaihd.net/static-ak/rsrc.php/v2/yE/r/tKlGLd_GmXe.png", :atenders => 94, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-10-25 14:35:31", :updated_at => "2012-10-25 14:35:31" },
  { :name => "M.A.N.D.Y | LIVIO & ROBY | SUNDECK | 22 NOVIEMBRE", :longitude => -70.57931169999999, :latitude => -33.3941375, :gmaps => true, :description => "Noche épica en Club Eve", :start_time => "2012-11-22 21:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-23 02:55:00", :address => "Hernán Prieto Vial 1720-1734, Vitacura, Santiago Metropolitan Region, Chile", :fb_id => 282810638486199, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "https://fbcdn-profile-a.akamaihd.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/203477_282810638486199_1925804277_q.jpg", :atenders => 119, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-10-25 14:35:35", :updated_at => "2012-10-25 14:35:35" },
  { :name => "ART DEPARTMENT (CREAMFIELDS SIDE SHOW) EN MACARENA CLUB!", :longitude => -70.5793533, :latitude => -33.3941681, :gmaps => true, :description => "MACARENA CLUB PRESENTA:\n\nART DEPARTMENT (CREAMFIELDS CHILE SIDE SHOW) \n\nJueves 08 de Noviembre.\n\nApertura Puertas: 22:00 hrs. \n\nCocktail 22:00 Hrs (Bocados / Ceviche / Coronas / Champagne)\n\n----------------------------------------------------\n\nBIO ART DEPARTMENT:\n\nArt Department es el proyecto conjunto del veterano Kenny Glasgow y el joven Jonny White. Ambos por separado ya han contado con unas carreras gozando de buena aceptación. El primero porque ha sido uno de los djs canadienses mas internacionales desde que comenzó a pinchar a finales de los 80 y el segundo se ha hecho un hueco en la escena gracias a su sello No.19. Aunque ambos se conocen desde hace tiempo ya que comparten ciudad (Toronto), no ha sido hasta el 2009 cuando se han juntado a trabajar en el estudio, y fue gracias a que Damian Lazarus les pidiera un remix de un tema de Riz MC para su sello Crosstown Rebels. Su único EP hasta la fecha, Vampire Nightclub / Without You (Crosstown Rebels) fue uno de los mas pinchados y aclamados del 2010 y están a punto de publicar su primer álbum, The Drawing Board, que sale en 2011 también a través del sello de Damian Lazarus. \n\nEnglish Version:\n\nArt Department is the brainchild of Canadian techno/house Legend Kenny Glasgow and Canada’s fastest rising star and No.19 label owner - Jonny White. As individuals both Kenny and Jonny have released countless critically acclaimed records and are regarded internationally as two of the most forward thinking, revolutionary underground producers out of North America. Kenny’s credentials date back to the late 80’s and include productions on Narcotic, Jinxx, his own Method 11/11 label and Turbo. Whilst White’s revered No.19 Music label along side a blindingly fast - growing discography have seen him rapidly rise to the forefront of the international scene.\n\nThe pair, despite being close friends and stalwarts in the Toronto electronic music scene for years, had not joined forces in the studio until only as recently as 2009, when Damian Lazarus called on them to remix Riz MC for his prestigious Crosstown Rebels Label. The result was an entirely new sound that drew cues from the best of both artists. It was a futuristic and raw, synth-driven, underground masterpiece, the start of a new idea and the birth of Art Department…\n\nBefore long the two were working full time in the studio to expand upon what they had created but now with a new focus… the concept for Art Department was to create a live dj/vocal performance based on the new sound they were beginning to produce and would feature Kenny Glasgow’s unique and sublime vocals that had been heard only 10+ years earlier on records like “Pressing On”. It wasn’t long before Damian heard what the pair had been working on and immediately offered them a deal with Crosstown Rebels that would include several singles, remixes and a full length album due out at the beginning of 2011.\n\nThe momentum continued and Art Department performed their first ever live show at the Crosstown Rebels Get Lost event at the 2010 WMC in front of a jam packed room, along side an A list cast of 17 artists from the label. DJ’s, promoters and party animals regarded the performance as one of the most ground-breaking & important shows at this years WMC…Simple label boss - Will Saul was quoted saying “the live show was the best thing we’ve heard since we heard Mathew Johnson for the first time…”. The follow up performance came the very next night at Jamie Jones & Lee Foss’ Hot Natured party where Art Department treated the enthusiastic crowd to a mind-bending dj set and secured their spot as residents for the much lauded Hot Natured brand.\n\nWith massive support from the rebel crew along with an exciting release schedule including collaborations with Seth Troxler, Jamie Jones and Soul Clap there is no doubt that this will be yet another inspired chapter in the story of these Canadian talents.\n\n----------------------------------------------------\n\nJOYE MITARAKIS:\n\nDespués de otro año más tocando en diversos clubes en Berlín, lo esperamos con una calurosa bienvenida en Macarena Club. \n\n----------------------------------------------------\n\nLINE UP:\n\nART DEPARTMENT\nhttps://www.facebook.com/artdepartmentmusic\nhttp://www.myspace.com/artdepartment\n\n\nJOYE MITARAKIS\nhttp://soundcloud.com/joyemitarakis\nhttp://www.myspace.com/mitarakis\n\n\n\n+ PRONTO MÁS INFORMACIÓN\n\n* MACARENA CLUB se Reserva el Derecho de Admisión.", :start_time => "2012-11-08 21:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-09 03:00:00", :address => "Hernán Prieto Vial 1720-1734, Vitacura, Santiago Metropolitan Region, Chile", :fb_id => 293230037444326, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "https://fbcdn-profile-a.akamaihd.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/211165_293230037444326_1031191182_q.jpg", :atenders => 286, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-10-25 14:35:38", :updated_at => "2012-10-25 14:35:38" },
