  { :name => "EVOL presents EUGENE MCGUINNESS", :longitude => -2.9768396, :latitude => 53.4089563, :gmaps => true, :description => "Sunday 11th November 2012\n\nEVOL presents\n\nEUGENE MCGUINNESS\nhttp://www.eugenemcguinness.net/\n\nWhen he was younger living in Liverpool he was the local poet laureate, now he's a wee bit older, living on the road he's become a full blown rocknroller...\n\nEugene has just released his fourth album on Domino Records entitled \"The Invitation to the Voyage\" and plays his first show in Liverpool since supporting White Denim at Liverpool Sound City and that was packed to the rafters.\n\nJoin him in celebration of the release of this monumental record.\n\nSupport\n\nCOVES\nhttp://covesband.com/\n&\nTHE DIRTY RIVERS\nhttp://soundcloud.com/the-dirty-rivers\n\nDoors 8pm - 11pm\n14+ show\nTickets £8 advance via http://bit.ly/PG5NW7 of in person O2 Academy Box Office, no booking fee on cash sales.\nOnline via Ticketweb / SEE / Ticketline\n\nO2 Academy Liverpool\n11 - 13 Hotham Street\nLiverpool\nL3 5UF\nwww.o2academyliverpool.com\n\nFor more info follow EVOL on Twitter @ClubEVOL\n\nListings\n\n24.10 Dry The River @ The Kazimier\n26.10 Dan Le Sac & Friends @ The Kazimier\n27.10 Two Gallants (USA) @ Leaf\n29.10 Clock Opera @ The Kazimier\n07.11 Ariel Pink’s Haunted Graffiti (USA) @ The Kazimier\n14.11 Mystery Jets @ The Kazimier\n15.11 Shabazz Palaces & THEEsatisfaction @ The Kazimier\n23.11 The Sundowners Single Launch @ Zanzibar Club\n27.11 Peace @ The Kazimier\n28.11 Purity Ring + Doldrums (Canada) @ The Kazimier\n29.11 Chain And The Gang (USA) @ The Shipping Forecast\n01.12 Band Of Skulls @ O2 Academy 1\n05.12 Chilly Gonzales @ Capstone Theatre\n06.12 The View @ O2 Academy 1\n15.12 Ian McNabb & Band @ The Kazimier\n11.05 ∆ @ O2 Academy 1\n\nwww.ticketweb.co.uk / www.seetickets.com / www.ticketline.co.uk\n ", :start_time => "2012-11-11 15:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-11 18:00:00", :address => "1-27 Bridport St, Liverpool, Merseyside L3 5QF, UK", :fb_id => 421438101251656, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "https://fbcdn-profile-a.akamaihd.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/276729_421438101251656_1711419506_q.jpg", :atenders => 36, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-10-25 15:06:51", :updated_at => "2012-10-25 15:06:51" },
  { :name => "Novochild en Chile (Santiago) + Ermitaño (CHI)", :longitude => -70.63762009999999, :latitude => -33.4370171, :gmaps => true, :description => "Después de presentar en distintos países del cono Sur su primer disco en 2010, Novochild vuelve con Waiting for a sign, su nuevo trabajo que presentará en Chile, Argentina y Uruguay. Tras recibir varios premios y reconocimientos en Alemania, la banda de rock progresivo-alternativo de Berlín es elegida como la revelación de la escena alemana. Considerada ya de ese modo en 2009 por los medios especializados de su país, tiene la particularidad de que –además del inglés y alemán- muchas de sus letras están cant...adas en castellano, idioma original de su cantante, el argentino Leandro Fest. El resto de la banda se compone por músicos berlineses, de distintas raíces: tres nacidos en la entonces Alemania Federal y otro en la Oriental. Esos orígenes tan disímiles–por Buenos Aires y lo que separó el muro-, le dan a la banda una identidad propia.\n“Yo me volví más puntual, más planificador. Ellos más espontáneos e improvisadores. Yo aprendí de ciertas estructuras, ellos escucharon nuevos ritmos. Viajamos mucho, compartimos muchas horas y ese intercambio, creo que se termina notando en la misma música de Novochild. Un intercambio que a veces se da en las mismas canciones, en las que podés escuchar español e inglés, e incluso alemán en una misma canción”, grafica Fest antes de cerrar la idea: \"Somos una banda alemana que además de inglés canta en español\". Frontman natural de la banda, el argentino en las giras toma un carácter central por el dominio del idioma, ya que además de Chile, Argentina y Uruguay, la banda se presenta habitualmente en distintas ciudades españolas. También el grupo toca normalmente en Suiza, República Checa Polonia y, por supuesto, Alemania, donde llegaron a tocar en el festival a beneficio gratuito más grande del país. La gira los tendrá otra vez en países en los que presentó dos años atrás su primera placa, First Day of Stay, y tendrá fechas junto a bandas locales en cada país. El tramo argentino será compartido en gran parte con los locales Eruca Sativa, de un progreso similar al evidenciado por Novochild en Berlín. “Ahora el bajista, Mamba, está tomando clases de español”, se alivia Fest, quien espera no ser el único interlocutor en esta segunda gira sudamericana.. “Creo que crecimos mucho. Si bien, mantenemos nuestro costado progresivo-experimental, logramos profundizar más las ideas y, a la vez, ser más concretos. En el primer disco nunca\nhubiéramos imaginado una canción de menos de cinco minutos. En el nuevo disco, nuestro primer single, En la red, no llega a los tres y, sin embargo, mantiene el sonido característico de Novochild”, explicó a Fest al comparar su primer disco y el que presentará en la región a partir de noviembre, Waiting For a Sign.\n\nwww.facebook.com/novochild\nwww.youtube.com/nchvideos\nwww.novochild.com\nwww.twitter.com/novochild\n\n#vuelvenovochild\n", :start_time => "2012-11-10 22:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-11 01:00:00", :address => "Crnel Santiago Bueras, Santiago, Santiago Metropolitan Region, Chile", :fb_id => 447962675249712, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "https://fbcdn-profile-a.akamaihd.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/203524_447962675249712_260661451_q.jpg", :atenders => 9, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-10-25 15:06:53", :updated_at => "2012-10-25 15:06:53" },
  { :name => "NORTH BY NORTH WEST 2012", :longitude => -2.9601363, :latitude => 53.41521299999999, :gmaps => true, :description => "NORTH BY NORTH WEST 2012 is set for Saturday 10th November 2012 in the grandest of halls: The Liverpool Olympia.\n\nA space not regularly used for this type of event over recent years but a space that boasts an amazing saga within Merseyside's history.\n\nThe ex Circus, Cinema, & Ballroom that has stood for over 100 years just outside of the city centres reach will be alive with the sound of MerseysideMusic. \nThe aim is to create one grand night with an invite extended to all to celebrate this summit that we feel is upon us in Merseyside 2012. Over the past couple of years we've seen a massive surge in our hometown with amazing things happening in every corner of the city and its surroundings, from the events already taken place to the birth and creation of new talent. On Saturday 10th November 2012 we bring you just the tip of the biggest iceberg we've hit since the titanic with appearances from The Tea Street Band, The Hummingbirds, By The Sea, The Red Suns,(newly billed) The Sundowners, Cold Shoulder, Broken Men, The Loud, Dead Dukes, Luke Fenlon (Sugermen), Midnight Playground, The Dead Velvets, DJ Sets from The Coral and more special guests yet to be announced.  Tickets are available from ticket line.co.uk & bidolito.co.uk as well as the Liverpool Olympia Box Office\n \nAdult 18+ = £10\nStudent/NUS = £8\nAge 14 - 18 = £6 \n\nDoors: 6pm til late!\n\nFacebook Event \nhttp://www.facebook.com/events/136864469792335/?fref=ts\n\nPromotional Video\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L1Jo1LZ3oY4\n\n____________________________________________\n\nCompared by BBC Radio Merseyside & BBC Introducing's\nDAVE MONKS!\n\nTHE TEA STREET BAND \nhttp://soundcloud.com/the-tea-street-band\nTHE HUMMINGBIRDS\nhttp://soundcloud.com/wearethehummingbirds\nTHE RED SUNS\nhttp://soundcloud.com/the-red-suns\nCOLD SHOULDER\nhttp://soundcloud.com/cold-shoulder\nBY THE SEA\nhttp://www.facebook.com/bytheseaband\nTHE SUNDOWNERS\nhttp://www.facebook.com/sundownersUK\nTHE LOUD\nhttp://thelouduk.blogspot.co.uk/\nBROKEN MEN\nhttps://vimeo.com/47011181\nDEAD DUKES\nhttp://www.deaddukesofficial.co.uk/\nLUKE FENLON (SUGERMEN)\nhttp://www.lukefenlon.com/\nTHE DEAD VELVETS\nhttp://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Dead-Velvets/267517659939358\nMIDNIGHT PLAYGROUND\nhttp://www.facebook.com/MidnightPlaygroundUK\n\nWith THE CORAL following up with a DJSet!\nplus more VERY SPECIAL GUEST announcements.\n\nWe'll also have a full vintage clothing fair held at the event so you get some retail therapy in between acts supplied by the wonderful Pillbox Vintage.\n\nTickets on sale now from bidolito.co.uk for just £10\nhttp://www.bidolito.co.uk/gig/north-north-west-2012\n\nTICKETS.\nhttps://www.ticketline.co.uk/order/tickets/13275023/liverpool-band-night-liverpool-olympia-2012-11-10-18-00-00\n\nhttp://www.bidolito.co.uk/gig/north-north-west-2012\n\n\n", :start_time => "2012-11-10 14:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-10 17:00:00", :address => "3 Lavan Close, Liverpool, Merseyside L6 2WQ, UK", :fb_id => 136864469792335, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "https://fbcdn-profile-a.akamaihd.net/hprofile-ak-snc7/373101_136864469792335_51498931_q.jpg", :atenders => 160, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-10-25 15:06:57", :updated_at => "2012-10-25 15:06:57" },
