  { :name => "Hurricane Sandy Relief Fundraiser @ Z Burger", :longitude => -77.0779862, :latitude => 38.9454616, :gmaps => true, :description => " Hurricane Sandy swept through this past weekend, leaving most of the Northeast without power, water, and shelter. Some of us whose families were severely impacted have gotten together in order to put together this fundraiser. Please come show your support for all those affected by this horrible disaster at ZBurger Wednesday, November 7 from 5 PM- 9 PM. Present the flier at Zburger (attached to this page also the default photo) and 20 percent of the money raised will be going to the American Red Cross. \n\nLet's show that the AU/Tenley community is thinking of our friends in this time of need. ", :start_time => "2012-11-07 17:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-07 21:00:00", :address => "4319 Wisconsin Ave NW, Washington, DC 20016, USA", :fb_id => 434738633242139, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/373293_434738633242139_321075704_q.jpg", :atenders => 283, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:13", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:13" },
  { :name => "Campus Diplomats: FALL FORUM 2012", :longitude => -82.34891879999999, :latitude => 29.6502481, :gmaps => true, :description => "Campus Diplomats are the official ambassadors to the Dean of Students Office, located in Peabody Hall. Our mission is to personalize the University through inclusive programing and an active presence in the University of Florida. This exclusive organization has been serving the Gator Nation since the 1980s. Through our programs we strive to enhance your experience here at the University of Florida. Some of our programs include: Family Weekend, AllUF, Welcome to the Sunshine State, and Apple 4U.\n\nAt Fall Forum, you will hear all about what we do and what it takes to become a Campus Diplomat. You will also learn about the application and interview process as well as ask questions and mingle with our current members! It's something you won't want to miss!\n\nIf you have any questions email diplomats@dso.ufl.edu or write here on the wall and we will get back to you!\n\nLooking forward to seeing you all there! We're so excited to meet you!", :start_time => "2012-11-14 18:30:00", :end_time => "2012-11-14 21:30:00", :address => "1578-1652 Gale Lemerand Dr, Gainesville, FL 32608, USA", :fb_id => 283344471783753, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/211173_283344471783753_1037827231_q.jpg", :atenders => 173, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:24", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:24" },
  { :name => "Election Night Non-Voting Get Together", :longitude => -77.04222899999999, :latitude => 38.9218822, :gmaps => true, :description => "When election time comes around, millions of Americans across the land will raise the cry: get out and vote! And those that don't are chastised as anti-American and apathetic, and are told they don't have the right to complain. \n\nThe truth is, many of us who don't vote aren't anti-American, aren't apathetic, and believe we have just as much a right as any to voice our opinions. \n\nEveryone has different reasons for not voting. Some dislike their options. Some wish to take a stand against the political system. Some don't support the majority-rule principle. \n\nIf you're a conscious non-voter and will not compromise your principles for the sake of political convenience, then come join friendly company this election night! We'll be gathering at Tryst Coffeehouse, Bar, and Lounge, from 6 to 8. We hope to see you there!", :start_time => "2012-11-06 19:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-06 21:00:00", :address => "2455 18th St NW, Washington, DC 20009, USA", :fb_id => 304911232956858, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc7/373161_304911232956858_74525183_q.jpg", :atenders => 10, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:30", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:30" },
  { :name => "Previa de mi cumple", :longitude => -71.59334129999999, :latitude => -33.0589542, :gmaps => true, :description => "Voy a celebrar la previa de mi cumple en el Bar Morena para el que se anima este jueves!!\n\nlos precios que vamos a tener son:\n- Pisco Ron y vodka a $2.000 (pero se separan en 2 vasos)\n- 2 pitcher por $5.000\n\nal que se anima esta totalmente invitado!!\n\nNos vemos!!", :start_time => "2012-11-08 20:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-08 23:00:00", :address => "Zegers 564, Valparaíso, Valparaíso Region, Chile", :fb_id => 548140498535118, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/277034_548140498535118_1131952850_q.jpg", :atenders => 22, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:33", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:33" },
  { :name => "Nic School Talent Show: Superheroes and Spirit Animals", :longitude => -78.92101450000001, :latitude => 36.0101359, :gmaps => true, :description => "Come out for a night of fun, laughs and drinks. Acts don’t have to be formal and are only limited by your creativity. Want to do a rendition of Gangnam style? Cartwheels? Bongos? Whatever you’d like to show off, we’d love to see it.\n\nEvent starts at 9pm and first act goes on at 9:30pm\nBest Act of the night wins a $50 tab for the Tavern.\n\nCost: None! \n\nCostumes: They are highly encouraged and open to creativity. Come dressed as your favorite superhero (or one the world has yet to meet). Anyone (audience and performers) can dress up, although performances do not need to relate to the theme.\n\nOther forms of participation\n1) Baking contest! Anonymous judging will decide the best dish, which will receive $25 to Whole Foods\n2) Come support your classmates\n3) Free drink tickets to early birds\n\nYours truly,\nNicholas School Student Council\n\nIF YOU WANT TO PARTICIPATE: If you plan to perform, you must email me before the event with your name(s), description of talent and any questions. If you are curious about performing, feel free to email me as well! (jessica.lam@duke.edu)", :start_time => "2012-11-15 21:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-16 00:00:00", :address => "1900 W Markham Ave, Durham, NC 27705, USA", :fb_id => 430376490353846, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/592187_430376490353846_1959856970_q.jpg", :atenders => 54, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:35", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:35" },
  { :name => "5th Annual SAF Lumberjack Party", :longitude => -78.896338, :latitude => 36.0040059, :gmaps => true, :description => "Calling all sons of beeches, fine pieces of ash, and other poplar people:\n\nSAF, AFE, and Sandford's annual Lumberjack Party is happening on Saturday, November 10th.\n\nCome out to Gate F at the Duke Forest to get back to the roots of Duke’s School of Forestry and celebrate the end of Forestry Week! \n\nThe best part? It’s all FREE!\n\nDress like a lumberjack: flannel and suspenders\nDrink like a lumberjack: kegs of beer and cider\nEat like a lumberjack: flapjacks and bacon for everybody!\nPlay like a lumberjack: we'll leave this a surprise\n\nParking will be at Gate 12 (next to Gate F where the festivities will be) off of 751. The gate is on the left in the cleared area underneath the power lines and will be marked with traffic cones. Taxis will be scheduled to arrive at the end of the evening for those who had a little too much to drive home.\n\nSo join us for an evening of music, games, and revelry you wooden want to miss!\n", :start_time => "2012-11-10 20:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-10 23:00:00", :address => "204 W Geer St, Durham, NC 27701, USA", :fb_id => 379909955421031, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/276430_379909955421031_564802947_q.jpg", :atenders => 100, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:37", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:37" },
  { :name => "Wild & Scenic Film Festival", :longitude => -78.90347, :latitude => 35.997782, :gmaps => true, :description => "Considered one of the nation’s premiere environmental and adventure film festival’s, this year’s films combine stellar filmmaking, beautiful cinematography and first-rate storytelling to inform, inspire and ignite solutions and possibilities to restore the earth and human communities while creating a positive future for the next generation.  Festival-goers can expect to see Award winning films about nature, community activism, adventure, conservation, water, energy and climate change, wildlife, environmental justice, agriculture, Native American and indigenous cultures.\n\nThis year’s selections will not only take audiences to some of the most remote and beautiful places on the planet, but introduce them to the magnificent animals that inhabit these places and the courageous individuals who are working to protect and preserve both for future generations.  The films instill a deep appreciation and a sense of wonder for the natural world that surrounds and supports us.\n\nTHURSDAY, NOVEMBER 8\nDoors open at 5:30pm; Films start at 6:30pm\nDurham Arts Council \n\nTickets on sale now: syrclswildscenicfilmfestival.eventbrite.com\n\nBenefiting the Environmental Internship Fund\n\nTo view trailers, visit: www.wildandscenicfilmfestival.org", :start_time => "2012-11-08 18:30:00", :end_time => "2012-11-08 21:30:00", :address => "120 Morris St, Durham, NC 27701, USA", :fb_id => 184503878353620, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/276735_184503878353620_395581716_q.jpg", :atenders => 54, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:41", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:41" },
  { :name => "Election Night Party", :longitude => -118.114818, :latitude => 33.931325, :gmaps => true, :description => "The Public Policy Studies Major's Union (PPSMU) is organizing a school-wide, non-partisan election night party in Sanford School of Public Policy! We'll have free food, free beer and plenty of TVs with different networks so you can watch the results on whichever channel you'd like. All students (undergraduate and graduate), faculty, and staff welcome. We hope to see you there!\n\nThe party is co-sponsored by: \n\nDuke University Union\nDuke Student Government\nGraduate and Professional Student Council\nDuke Political Science Students Association\nDuke College Republicans\nDuke Democrats\nDuke Political Union", :start_time => "2012-11-06 20:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-07 00:00:00", :address => "9447 Firestone Blvd, Downey, CA 90241, USA", :fb_id => 269073223196029, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/373293_269073223196029_822047138_q.jpg", :atenders => 408, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:43", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:07:43" },
