  { :name => "ICE Diwali 2012", :longitude => -84.383282, :latitude => 33.7616807, :gmaps => true, :description => "Tickets:\nICE Diwali ticket sales start Thursday, October 18th in the DUC Coke Commons for $25. Please have Student ID and exact change (cash only) when approaching the ticketing table. Buy your tickets before they sell out. Only a limited number of spots available. Ticket includes transportation, traditional Indian dinner, cultural dance performances, open dance floor, and unforgettable memories.\n\n\n\nVenue:\nHilton Downtown Atlanta\n255 Courtland Street NE\nAtlanta GA, 30303\n\n\n\nAttire:\nThe attire for Emory ICE Diwali 2012 is deemed formal. Suit and tie or traditional Indian clothing is required for men. Formal dresses or traditional Indian clothing is required for women. No hats, jeans, or sneakers are allowed.\n\n\n\nTransportation:\nICE Diwali Shuttles will be providing transportation to and from the Hilton for ICE Diwali 2012. The first shuttle leaves at 5:30 pm on November 10, 2012 from the Woodruff Circle shuttle stop. Shuttles will run at 5:30, 5:40, 5:50, 6:20, 6:30, 6:40, 7:10, 7:20, and 7:30. Please keep your desired shuttle time in mind. Signups will be available at the time of ticket purchase. \n\nFor students wishing to drive themselves to the event, valet parking is available at the Hilton for $10. \n\n\n\nCultural Performances:\nSaRaas\nSavera\nKarma & PersuAsian (fusion)\nTrickaNomeTry & Sitara (fusion)\nZeebah & Azaadi (fusion)\nSenior Class 2013 Dance\n\n\n\nDinner:\nViceroy; Royal Indian Dining\n\"Our vision is to simplify Indian cooking and bring you back to the basics with nutrition, quality, flavor, aroma and taste. Our spice blends fresh ingredients and your imagination which will transform your craving into simple and satisfying cuisine\"\n\n\n\nProgram:\nEmory ICE Diwali 2012 will begin at 6:30pm and will promptly end at 1:00am. Please plan your night accordingly. Doors will close at 8:00pm sharp. Please arrive early to enjoy the cocktail hours from 6:00pm-8:00pm. If there is a time conflict, contact one of the ICE Executive Board Officers.\n\n\n\nReminders:\n*Please bring your Emory ICE Diwali 2012 ticket and your Emory student ID. We will be checking them at the shuttle stop & collecting tickets them at the door. \n\n*Please remember that the ticket issued to you at the time of purchase is linked to your name. Therefore, you cannot trade or lose your ticket as you will not be allowed entry. \n\n*If your ticket has been lost or you wish to sell your ticket, please contact one of the ICE Officers. Thank you and we hope you enjoy the experience. \n\n\n\nContact:\nPlease email Mythilee Kugathasan (mkugath@emory.edu) or Louisa Keeler (lkeeler@emory.edu) with questions! ", :start_time => "2012-11-10 18:30:00", :end_time => "2012-11-11 01:00:00", :address => "255 Courtland St NE, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA", :fb_id => 437955899574352, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc7/373496_437955899574352_122984538_q.jpg", :atenders => 437, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:11:22", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:11:22" },
