  { :name => "LMS- Val Thorens Winter Trip", :longitude => 6.5800259, :latitude => 45.2978758, :gmaps => true, :description => "                               ******SOLD OUT******\n\nLeeds Met Snowsports are proud to announce that for our annual winter trip we will be taking you lovely lot to Val Thorens. Needless to say IT’S GOING TO BE BIG! \n\nImportant facts:\n•      4th -12th January 2013\n•      Val Thorens, France\n•      Only £339!\n \nWhat’s included:\n•      Accommodation (ski in- ski out. In the heart of VT)\n•      Transport (Executive coach with the usual fancy dress)\n•      Six day lift pass\n•      Breakfast (This will include tea, coffee, sugar, butter, jam,       chocolate spread, cereal, milk and fresh bread delivered each morning.)\n•      Holiday T-shirt\n•      Exclusive drinks discounts in various bars\n•      *An amazing holiday that you will not forget!\n \nVAL THORENS:\nIf you've not been to Val T then you've not yet really been to the Alps. Highest resort in Europe. The 3 Valleys. 600km of piste. 6 snow parks. Bar 360. Malaysia (Highest club in Europe) . It not only ticks every box you need from a holiday, it smashes them into the ground and beats them around the face.\n\n'First lift, last orders' is the only way to make the most of Val Thorens, with the largest array of bars and the exhilarating nightlife coming second only to the amazing 600km of jaw-dropping pisted runs. As part of the largest linked ski resort in the world with a huge network of blue and green runs, it's perfect for beginners as they can really make the most of the mountain. If you're a pro then the copious parks (including the famous DC Park just over in Meribel) and the abundance of challenging black runs will keep you more than entertained.\n\nVT Truly is a bullet-proof resort and one of the most student friendly. NUCO working closely with the LMS committee will make sure that there is never a dull moment from our freestyle jam sessions, mountain meal to wacky fancy dress themes most nights.\n \nOptional extras:\n‘Meal on the mountain’ – LMS highly recommend this, as it’s the icing on the cake to a great day’s skiing! We all gather up the mountain, have some exciting food, get a bit silly LMS style followed by a wobbly ski down into VT.\nLessons and equipment hire – For anyone who is a complete beginner, fear not NUCO can sort all your lessons and equipment through the booking page. Skiing and Boarding holidays are a unique holiday altogether and chances are you're going to get hooked!\n\nBook via…\n\n1.\tCreate a NUCO profile at: https://accounts.nucotravel.com/create\n2.\tBook the LMS holiday at: https://booking.nucotravel.com/sy/leedsmet\n\nGet booking guys! (Places are limited) \n\n*The first 100 to book will receive a free LMS goodie bag including a free club t- shirt\n\nSee you there...\n", :start_time => "2013-01-04 11:00:00", :end_time => "2013-01-12 06:00:00", :address => "Place des Arolles, Refuge du Col du Palet, 73440 Saint-Martin-de-Belleville, France", :fb_id => 121315721350357, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/188061_121315721350357_1802330975_q.jpg", :atenders => 181, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:12:21", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:12:21" },
