  { :name => "ILL CLINTON - ILL CLINTON (OBAMA) | OFFICIAL VIDEO | LIFE CHANGING AND MIND-BLOWING", :longitude => -84.3895622, :latitude => 33.7549383, :gmaps => true, :description => "ILL CLINTON - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g68ys2vkyjI&feature=youtu.be\n\nThe Elite Atlanta Presents: \nAn Abstract Visual from Atlanta Hip Hop Duo ILL CLINTON for their self-titled first single.\nDebut Mixtape from ILL CLINTON expected for 2012 release. \n\nDirected By: A Dreamers Visual\nProduced By: Blake Perry and Brennan Perry of The Elite Atlanta. 2012\nPresidential Productions.", :start_time => "2012-12-31 02:00:00", :end_time => "2013-01-01 02:00:00", :address => "40 Peachtree St NW, Georgia State University, Atlanta, GA 30303, USA", :fb_id => 409735325753467, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/373321_409735325753467_494446672_q.jpg", :atenders => 0, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:14", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:14" },
  { :name => "Akara (1st Time in ATL) + Skytree / Agobi Project / Kolourz / Distopia @ Asylum", :longitude => -84.34452089999999, :latitude => 33.7392378, :gmaps => true, :description => "Buy Tickets: http://akara.eventbrite.com/\n----------------------------------\n\n.: Akara (DJ-Set)  - (Los Angeles, CA) \n\n.: Skytree  - (Minneapolis, MN)\n\n.: Agobi Project  - (Asheville, NC)\n\nLocal Support: \nKolourz + Distopia  \n----------------------------------\n\n\n\n\nYou have been invited to join us in a divine gathering to travel through time and space, different dimensions, and realms while exploring love, reality, thought, and consciousness. \n\nThis spiritual awakening will be full of enlightenment and we promise to keep the \"intimate\" vibe going for this one with some chill music and some chill people.\n\nWe are going all night from 9-4am \n\nLive Painting\n+\nHeady Vendors.... as always ;)\n\n- See you there family - Great way to relax after finals week -\n\nOnly $8 in Advance / $10 at the door \nBuy Tickets: http://akara.eventbrite.com/\n\n\n\n\n----------------------------------\nPresented by: Locus Promotions \n\nFacebook.com/LocusPromo\nTwitter.com/LocusPromo\nLocusPromo.com\n----------------------------------\n\nArtist Bio(s)\n\n.: Akara :. (Re:Evolution Media)\nhttp://akaraproject.com/\nCreated by Joshua Penman, a conservatory-trained classical composer turned electronic producer, Akara’s mystical dance ﬂoor symphonies are songs of luminous extradimensional beings, sung across the veil of reality. Akara's music is intricately scored for a live ensemble of classical musicians and the haunting vocals of Femke Weidema. It is a deep, mystical journey into another world, fusing an enormously wide palette of musical inﬂuences with a generous helping of bass. Filigreed and beautiful and immersive, there is nothing like Akara. \n\n.: Skytree :. (Re:Evolution Media)\nwww.soundcloud.com/skytree\nSkytree, aka Evan Snyder, started recording music at the age of 15, after the loan of a beaten Tascam tape deck cracked open the world of multi-track recording. Rough mix tapes followed, looping degraded swatches of guitar and keys over cheap drum machines. The Skytree name found its way onto mixes by accident initially, suggesting a sound both old and new, rooted in the Earth and branching into the cosmos.\n\n.: Agobi Project :.\nhttp://www.reverbnation.com/theagobiproject\nThe band provides a myriad of genre that pushes the boundaries of electronic dance music, with elements of jazz, hip hop, drum and bass, house, electro among others. It is a delicately balanced mix of high energy live drums, state of the art laptop production and seasoned guitar wizardy. With this synthesis, Agobi has gained recognition from a wide range of audiences and scenes. The band strives to ensure that each show is not just a musical experience, but a celebration of art of all forms. With this in mind in Agobi's mission, a positive, free spirited, healing and purely magical experience has resulted every time they take the stage.\n\n.: Kolourz:.\nhttp://kolourzmusic.com/\nClassically trained in guitar and jazz performance Zach King, aka Kolourz, is making a name for himself in the constantly evolving electronic music scene.  Primary influences such as Flying Lotus, Nosaj Thing, and Daedelus have helped shaped his eclectic style and jazzy groove.\n\n.: Distopia :.\nAs the  project continues to grow, more influences have been  established to create the sound  that is in the works. With Funk, Jazz, Southern Rock, Progressive Jam, Electronic, and even a little swing. The overall goal of the members is to have fun doing what they love, and that is playing live music.", :start_time => "2012-12-14 21:00:00", :end_time => "2012-12-15 04:00:00", :address => "543 Flat Shoals Ave SE, Atlanta, GA 30316, USA", :fb_id => 122584577895697, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/261185_122584577895697_2067468151_q.jpg", :atenders => 120, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:18", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:18" },
  { :name => "Call of Booty Feat. Heroes X Villains Novem, 23rd", :longitude => -84.344734, :latitude => 33.73925030000001, :gmaps => true, :description => "GET YOUR PRESALEShttp://callofbooty.eventbrite.com/\n$5 FOR GIRLS UNTIL MIDNIGHT $10 AFTER// GUYS $10 ALLNIGHT\n$35 VIP COMES WITH ARTIST MEET AND GREET AND BOTTLE SERVICE\nSo 1332 Entertainment is at it again!! Bringing Atlanta one the hottest parties in town. Call of Booty will be turned into a seasonal event only coming to Atlanta 3 times a year, YEAH THATS RIGHT 3 TIMES A YEAR!! And ladies dont forget about the infamous booty competition in which the winner will receive a cash prize and 3 free tickets to any 1332 show for the next year!!\n\nNOW LETS GET TO OUR KILLER LINEUP!!!\n\nHEROES X VILLAINS-(Dubstep / Trap Music / Electro / Luxury Trap) \nMad Decent / Dim Mak / Circle Managment\nhttp://twitter.com/WE_ARE_HXV\nhttp://soundcloud.com/heroesxvillains\nhttp://heroesxvillains.tumblr.com\nhttp://youtube.com/HeroesxVillains\nhttp://vimeo.com/heroesxvillains\nhttp://myspace.com/weareheroesandvillains\nhttp://rcrdlbl.com/artists/Heroes__Villains\nhttp://theoverthrow.com\nhttp://therebelbasemgmt.com\n\n“Armed with this experience, roots in punk/hardcore and an appreciation for Southern rap music, Heroes x Villains start their ascent with warbling, bass heavy, electronic dance music remixes of Waka Flocka Flame's 'Oh Let's Do It' and Gucci Mane's 'Lemonade'. These, a remix of Lil' Jon and Diplo's 'U Don't Like Me' and several others make up 'We Off That,' their first mixtape which garners critical acclaim.\n\nLess speakers burst into flames these days but Heroes x Villains DJ sets remain as caustic as ever. Stage diving and raucous mosh pits are regular occurrences; champagne spraying in every direction and half naked women moving in ways their parents wouldn't likely approve of come standard. The raw, occult like energy and track selection is a manifestation of how Disaster and fans of Heroes x Villains choose to live: shameless, unrepentant, maximalist hedonism. \n\nHeroes x Villains barreled into 2012 as diverse and dangerous as ever. Beginning in early January, they introduced the weekly 'BLXRRD OXT' series, manipulating records like Young Jeezy's ode to intoxication 'WXY 2 GXNE' and England's dark pop princess Charlie XCX 'NUXLEAR SEAXONX' into soundtracks for a haunting, drug-addled haze. \n\nAnd in February, showcasing the two year progression of Southern rap music fusing with electronic dance elements, comes rising Atlanta rap group FKi's mixtape 'Transformers In The Hood' produced by Diplo, Heroes x Villains and Atlanta EDM producer Mayhem.\n\nWith genre-bending, rule breaking unpredictability as their calling card, it's pointless to attempt to figure out what Heroes x Villains may do next... best to just sign the waiver and enjoy the ride.\n\nSNELLVILLAIN-(Dubstep/Electronica/Hip Hop)\nFreakstep Records\nhttps://www.facebook.com/pages/SnellVillain/212185138796603\nwww.soundcloud.com/snellvillain\n\nFresh off the Hostile Takeover Tour with Tech N9ne and Machine Gun Kelly and winning Creative Loafing Atlanta's \"Best Local DJ\" award, Corey Herrin, aka SnellVillain, is a music producer/DJ out of Atlanta, Ga. He has had the opportunity to share the stage with multiple international headliners including Cookie Monsta, Liquid Stranger, Ajapai, Gramatik, Run DMT, Virus Syndicate, Wick-It The Instigator, Hellfire Machina, Mochipet, Mantis etc. With his infectious stage presence and his never ending urge to bring you the freshest, top quality originals, remixes, and live mashups there is no telling what the future may hold.\n\nDJ NUK-(Dubstep/Drumstep/Drum&Bass/Bass Music)\nFilth FM / Trillitary\nhttp://www.soundcloud.com/dj-nuk\n\nDJ NuK is a 29 yearold producer/DJ out of the Dirty South (Birmingham, AL/Atlanta, GA) DJ NuK has been on his quest to bring music to the masses for almost 15 years.. He has played almost every type of electronic music through the years (trance, breaks, house, progressive, dubstep, d&b), along with years of playing in metal and punk rock bands. Bands always seem to go their separate ways after a while, so NuK decided to go at it alone about 10 years ago, when he asked his folks for a set turntables for Christmas. He had never really taken the art of DJing seriously until about 2 years ago, but since then, he has been on the grind, non-stop, playing shows and promoting. He is quickly gaining recognition all over the Southeastern US, and one thing is for sure, he's tough to beat when it comes to energy, track selection, and mixing. DJ NuK is a resident of Trillitary Atlanta and Atlanta Bass Wars. He also has a weekly show on www.filth.fm on Wednesday nights 9-11pm EST. When NuK is behind the decks, look out.\n\nOculus-(Bass Music)\n\nThe Snacks-(dubstep x rap x indie x trap)\nFreakstep Records\n\n", :start_time => "2012-11-23 22:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-24 03:00:00", :address => "Stokeswood Ave SE@Portland Ave SE, Atlanta, GA 30316, USA", :fb_id => 460367907347567, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/373021_460367907347567_710019152_q.jpg", :atenders => 88, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:20", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:20" },
  { :name => "Sumilan | Futexture | Distopia (Full Band + Live-PA) @ Five Spot", :longitude => -84.35027199999999, :latitude => 33.76417, :gmaps => true, :description => "Sumilan\nFutexture (NC)\nDistopia  (Live-PA + full band sets)\n\nTicketing info: (http://tinyurl.com/8anczqo)\n\nAdvance: 7$\nDay of Show: 10$\n\nExtra Lighting and Visuals by:\n.:Captivating Light Designs:.\n (so you know it'll be dope)\n\nLive Painting\n\nVendors\n(anyone interested in setting up should message us)\n\n--------------------------------\nSumilan\nhttp://sumilan.com/\n\nFutexture \nhttp://soundcloud.com/futexture\n\nDistopia\nhttp://archive.org/details/DISTOPIA2012-08-10", :start_time => "2012-11-23 21:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-24 00:00:00", :address => "1117 Euclid Ave NE, Atlanta, GA 30307, USA", :fb_id => 411064505608213, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/373293_411064505608213_1717923132_q.jpg", :atenders => 107, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:22", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:22" },
  { :name => "Georgia Tech Taylor Trudeau Cycle for Life", :longitude => -84.4039701, :latitude => 33.775735, :gmaps => true, :description => "Taylor Trudeau Cycle for Life was created in memory of Taylor Trudeau, a University of New Hampshire Pi Kappa Alpha brother who passed away in August 2008 after fighting a year-long battle with Leukemia. On Sunday, November 18th, PIKE will be holding a 12 hour stationary bike marathon at the GT Campus Recreation Center. 100% of proceeds of this event will go toward the MD Anderson Center, a leading institution in the fields of Leukemia, Lymphoma, and Melanoma Research. A donation of $10 will get you a wrist band, raffle ticket, and spot on a bike for half an hour.\n\nThe brothers of Georgia Tech Pi Kappa Alpha invite you to come out and support a good cause. Together we can work out and work toward finding a cure for Leukemia, Lymphoma and Melanoma.\n\nIf you are interested in signing up, contact the brother who invited you or email Zurain Hassan at zhassan3@gatech.edu.", :start_time => "2012-11-18 09:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-18 21:00:00", :address => "750 Ferst Dr NW, Atlanta, GA 30318, USA", :fb_id => 491455960888430, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/276911_491455960888430_1941774975_q.jpg", :atenders => 55, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:25", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:25" },
  { :name => "DAYGLOW | THE .E.N.D. TOUR | Saturday November 10th 2012", :longitude => -84.129752, :latitude => 33.957853, :gmaps => true, :description => "TICKETS & HEADLINERS TBA SOON!\n\nALL NEW 2012 THE E.N.D. TOUR\n(Electronic.Never.Dies)\n\nLIFE IN COLOR (DAYGLOW)\n\n––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––\n––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––\nAbout:\n\nVarious ancient cultures throughout history have predicted 2012 as the end of civilization. While this may mark the end of an era, we believe as the year draws to a close, the world is only gearing up for a new day. 2012 The E.N.D (Electronic Never Dies) is more than just a mere slogan, this is a movement. This is our time. To every beginning there is an end, and a chance for a Rebirth. Because, in The E.N.D we are not our jobs, our failures or our fears, we are every note of every song that made us close our eyes, reach for the sky and know we were home.\n\nWith The E.N.D. Tour, we will have unprecedented production and never-before-seen live performances. We are taking a unified stance & upholding our beliefs, that love, expression, music, creativity & most of all paint will be the only forces that will survive into the next generation of Life in Color. Electronic Never Dies, so embrace it like it's your last opportunity to celebrate. #LIFEINCOLOR\n\nLast tour we sold out over 70 cities! It was Dayglow's most successful tour including international markets in Europe and South America. This tour we are back, with more cities and our largest production and show yet!\n\nBe part of the new music culture, be part of Dayglow.\n\n––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––\n––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––\n\nVisit Dayglow Online:\n\n• Website: http://www.dayglowtour.com/\n• Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/dayglowevent\n• Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/dayglowtour\n• Youtube: http://www.youtube.com/dayglowtour\n\n––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––\n––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––\n\nLIVE LIFE IN COLOR\n#lifeincolor", :start_time => "2012-11-10 23:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-11 04:00:00", :address => "2075 Market St, Duluth, GA 30096, USA", :fb_id => 455589321138746, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/592069_455589321138746_483903868_q.jpg", :atenders => 72, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:27", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:27" },
  { :name => "IRIS: ESP101 [Learn to Believe] | DUBTRIBE SOUND SYSTEM (LIVE) | SAT NOV 10", :longitude => -84.3459015, :latitude => 33.8281501, :gmaps => true, :description => "ADV $10 Presale ON SALE! | $15 No line Advanced \nTix: http://irispromotion.eventbrite.com\n \nIRIS Promotion & The IRIS Girls team up with Madhatter Promote Group to bring you a very special ESP101[Learn To Believe] Featuring special guest:\n \nDUBTRIBE SOUND SYSTEM - SAT NOV 10\n \nJoin us for a very special night, after almost a 3 year sabbatical, Dubtribe Soundsystem returns for a rare south east appearance at ESP 101! There is no other live act that cann create such an unstoppable and infectious energy for your spirit as well as your mind other than Dubtribe Sound System.\n Moonbeam and Sunshine have worked at a creative partnership for well over a decade and have found that while some prefer a formula, they are constantly pushing themselves, and re-inventing the sound that has become not only the DSS experience, but also influenced modern electronic music in general.\n There are no set positions, or rules. They do not imagine themselves as anything other than lovers of music, and the indescribable high that comes from invoking dancing to the sound of your heart, your inner fire, your unexpressed thoughts and feeling that peel off your head like the skin of an onion while youpractice a little more disco kung foo. \n\nW/ heavy support from\n \n-- RL Shine\n \n-- Sikora\n \n-- Corey Von Waters\n \n-- Ralph & Louie w/ Live percussion\n \n-- Next A kin & Mean Mug\n \n-- Doughboy\n \n-- Casper\n \n-- Brian Tedder's Silent Disco\n \n-- V3rsatile\n \nFeaturing: 4 separate atmospheres with booming Turbosound systems along with the most amazing and unique laser, lighting, and visual experiences brought to you by Area 51. Outside Terrace & VIP Lounges | Silent Disco |  Cryo blasts | free giveaways + More\n\nIRIS UPCOMING EVENTS: \n \nOctober:\n --Sat Oct 13: The Reunion II w/ Baby Anne, Bad Robotz & Mantis!!!! MY BIRTHDAY PARTY (YESSSS) \n --Sat Oct 20: The Pink Party (Beatz 4 Boobz) w/ J- Rabbit!!!!! \n --Sat Oct 27: VERY Special Halloween ESP101 Edition\n \nNovember:\n--Sat Nov 3: Q-BIK MUSIK!!!!! The #1 Australlian D&B/Drumstep act \n--Sat Nov 10: IRIS & MADDHATTER Productions team up for the VERY FIRST time to bring you: DUBTRIBE SOUND SYSTEM - LIVE (This is VERY special and VERY rare Atlanta performance) \n--Sat Nov 17: Bad Robotz & Eddie Gold\n--Sat Nov 24: HOT PINK DELOREAN!!!!\n \nDecember:\n--Sat Dec 01: Cyberoptics\n--Sat Dec 08: Mantis\n--Sat Dec 29: IRIS Pre-NYE party \n \nMON Dec 31: IRIS NYE EXTRAVAGANZA ♥ —\n \n--------------BIOS----------------\n \n:::: DUBTRIBE SOUND SYSTEM LIVE\n \nFrom 1990 to 2005 Dubtribe Sound System, husband and wife Sunshine and Moonbeam Jones, gathered friends and family together and traversed the planet performing house music live for millions of people.\n \nAllied with sit in and bring along percussionists, poets, painters, singers, and other musicians including Ray Lee, Nicky Sick, Babatunde, Primo Navaro, Matthew Brubeck, Karen Pfister, Chadwick Justin Minor, Richard Henry Scott, Lumo, Spiral Formatt, DJ Collage, Toast, Raymond St. Martin, DJ Lapaix, Kevin Wilson, and many others along the way, Dubtribe brought the idea that anything is possible, and that anyone can rise up and create art, political protest, and personal expression in the environment of DJ culture, rave, and night club or warehouse with a few simple devices and fire in your heart.\n \nThey arrived at a time when the world was in turmoil, the rave was a new idea which empowered people to gather and dance. Few followed the example set by Dubtribe, but many people were inspired to find their own road.\n \nDubtribe Sound System performed their final live concert at Cielo, in New York City on December 1st 2005. Many friends and family were in attendance, it was the perfect ending to a wonderfully indepenent, situationist, and punk rock road far too few people choose to travel with the passion and love that Sunshine and Moonbeam have.\n \nMay the beach always appear before you as the most beautiful dance floor in the world. Open up your mind, open up your heart, open up your hands, open up your mouth, open up your life, and set your spirit free.\n \n\n \n::::RL SHINE   \nKristen Sheehan, aka RL Shine has been popping up all over the map in the past 3 years from GA to NY and creeping into the midwest and beyond in 2012. She's shared the bill with acts including Young Guru, DJ Clockwork, Mac Miller, Porter Robinson, Nit Grit, Two Fresh, Will Clark, NY's long standing event, Concrete Jungle, Dara, Benga, Starkey, Heroes & Villains, Mayhem, Street Lurkin', Kid Cedek and many more.\n\n\n \n\n------ SCROLL TO BOTTOM TO READ THE REST OF OUR TALENT & RESIDENT DJ'S BIOS -----\n \n \n:::::::::::::::::::::::::: ABOUT ESP 101:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::\n \nESP101 is truly LEGENDARY and was instrumental in developing many of your favorite DJs, Light techs, Sound techs, Music Producers, Dancers! IRIS Promotion and The IRIS Girls are beyond thrilled to be able to provide you with the new chapter in this magical night. Prepare to experience that magical vibe and energy that everyone talks about but rarely is experienced; prepare for THE ONE AND ONLY\n \nESP101 was built on providing the VERY best in production for the VERY best \"locals\" in the land, Atlanta \"locals,\" THE very best talent the world has to offer...period!\n \nThe very best in EVERY genre of EDM: Electro,Drum & Bass, BASS Music, Breaks, DubStep, Trance, House, Hip Hop (old,middle,new school)\n \nAt ESP101 you will experience many old school DJs, many new school DJs, many big named DJs, many fresh out the box DJs, but ALL with one thing in common.... TALENT\n \nEACH & EVERY SATURDAY night IRIS brings you a FULL Production event that will BLOW YOUR MIND with the HIGHEST QUALITY EVERYTHING at the most reasonable price possible!!!!\n \n:::>18+ :::>>>>>>>>>>>>YES\n:::>21+ to drink, 4 full bars :::>>>>>>>YES\n:::>open VERY LATE:::>>>>>YES\n:::>TURBO SOUND :::>>>>>>YES\n:::>Custom Lasers & Lighting by Area 51 Presents:::>>>>>>YES\n:::>Cryogenic Guns:::>>>>>>YES\n:::>Fire Performers:::>>>>>YES\n:::>Large Outside Deck w/ sound:::>>>>>YES\n:::>3 different Atmospheres of Sound & Lighting:::>>>>YES\n:::>Stilt walkers:::>>>>>>>>>YES\n:::>Confetti Cannons:::>>>>>>>YES\n:::>Bottle Service Available:::>>>>>>>YES\n:::>Goldmeat:::>>>>>>>>>>>YES\n:::>Friendly,firm,& familiar IRIS security:::>>>>>YES\n:::>Amazing Hoopers:::>>>>>>>YES\n:::>Breakers:::>>>>>>YES\n:::>Aerialists:::>>>>>>>>YES\n:::>WINNING:::>>>>>>>YES\n:::>True Master of Ceremony:::>>>>>>>YES\n:::>Amazing custom decorations:::>>>>>>YES\n:::>Plenty of CLEAN bathrooms:::>>>>>>YES\n:::>GO GO dancers:::>>>>>>>>>>>YES\n:::>FTQ:::>>>>>>>>>>>YES\n:::>VIP Rooms Chillin w/Talent:::>>>>>>YES\n:::>TONS of absolutely FREE secured parking:::>>>>>>YES\n:::>Valet parking available:::>>>>>>>>>YES\n:::>Open Kitchen w/ great food:::>>>>>>>>>>YES\n:::>Thickest IRIS old school vibe:::>>>>>YES\n:::>PARTY w/ THE BEAUTIFUL IRIS GIRLS:::>>>>>>>>>>>>YES\n:::>BEST TALENT ::>>>>>>>>>> YES\n:::>VERY BEST CROWDS:::>>>>>>>>>>>YES\n \nIRIS loves you and it shows!!!!!!!!!!!!\n \nEach and every Saturday night @ RUSH\nWe bring you the very best in a locals showcase with the very best in sound, lighting, lasers, and performances each and every Saturday night. We will have A LOT of HUGE talent coming in as well to make the night that much more special. We thank you for the continued support over the many years and we will do our best to bring it to you the very best way we know how at the lowest price we can. The ONLY way, the RIGHT way, the IRIS way. We will continue to try to make you feel at home, where we call, THE UNDERGROUND!\n \nIris is about bringing light to the scene and creating the THICKEST vibe cocktail possible under one roof. We produce only the highest quality events and work with INTEGRITY, RESPECT, INTELLIGENCE, and SOLIDARITY... there are many other things Iris stands for as well. You will find that out as you get to know us.. IRIS - \"For those that know\" - MUCH LOVE TO YOU ALL BECOME A FAN of Iris Promotion and The Iris Girls\n \nMUCH LOVE AS ALWAYS,\nThe IRIS Family\nwww.facebook.com/irispromo\nwww.facebook.com/irisgirls\n \n\n:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::// PRESALES // :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::\n \n$10 Advanced Get them while they last (hint…hurry)\n$15 NO LINE Advanced | $20 AT DOOR\n \n(A very limited amount of $15 tickets will be held at the door. Get there early!)\n \n\n$35 FULL ACCESS VIP - Separate VIP NO LINE- Separate designated VIP areas w/ TALENT and plenty of seating and elbow room. VERY LIMITED SOLD\n::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::\n \nVENUE: RUSH aka \"The IRIS\" \n2715 Buford Hwy NE, Atlanta, GA 30305\nhttp://www.facebook.com/RushLounge +-> for Pics & Video\n \nIf it is SATURDAY night…. You KNOW where to be for the very dopest party of the month.. @ RUSH aka \"THE NEW IRIS\"\n \nFREE SECURED PARKING\nFREE SECURED PARKING \nFREE SECURED PARKING \nFREE SECURED PARKING\n \n::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::\n \nThis SATURDAY WEEKLY EVENT is for all you BASS HEADZ! \nDubstep | Drum & Bass | Electro | Breaks | House | Progressive House\n \n \n \n---------------- BIOGRAPHY'S OF OUR AMAZING TALENT ------------------\n \nSupport your locals \"the best talent in the land\"\n \n:::::::::::::: IRIS RESIDENTZ::::::::::::::::::::::\n \n:::: SIKORA       Original IRIS ::::Breakbeat, Drum & Bass, Dubstep Music \nIris ESP resident, DJ Sikora's first show was with Iris ESP at the Church in 1999. Since then he has been shaking asses and bringing people into the scene. Sikora is known for his smooth mixing and his ability to take the crowd on journey they won't forget. Check out Sikora live, for a performance you don't want to miss. To get a taste of what to expect you can go to the iTunes store and search DJ Sikora Podcast to download all his new and old mixes for free.http://www.facebook.com/pages/DJ-Sikora/136534406388500 \n\n\n:::: RALPH & LOUIE   Right Left Studios / IRIS / RAAW) - Atlanta, GA\n When we hit the decks at any event it is known that from that point on the crowd is in our hands. For over 18 years each these 2 seasoned DJs have rocked dance floors across the nation and have joined forces to bring your their new brain child.. RALPH & LOUIE! While feeding off each others energy and mastering the EQ and effects you will know there style is different than what you have heard before.. And if thats not enough and you are lucky enough to catch a set when they include live instruments such as Drums, Didgeridoo, Guitars, horns and more.. you will know why you are scheduling to see there next show in advanced.. Welcome to the minds of Ralph & Louie!!\n \nhttp://www.facebook.com/RalphAndLouie\n \n \n \n:::: CASPER     Affiliations - Iris Original, Bass Wars, Underground Syndicate\n \nSince 1995 Ryan Harrison otherwise known by the monikers Casper and Saturat3d Phat has been involved with the Dance Music movement. In 1997 his Dedication to the scene and passion for the music would lead him behind the decks. Two years later he had earned residencies with Iris Promotions, Viynl Boy, 421 entertainment and various other promoters and clubs in Atlanta. His ability to keep the crowd hype and rock the dance floor was all that was needed to take him all over the Country to play alongside many of the top dance music artists in the world. Known as a turntable terror with layered mixing and battle style Cuttin and scratchin he always brings it funky and fresh. In 2003 his first production work\" Right Now/Asteroid\" with Dj Neutron & The West City AllStars was released on 20K Freaks Records with great response. He has since had hundreds of remixes and original tracks drop. With no plans to slow down this Dj, producer and promoter continues his quest to entertain crowds everywhere!!!\n \n\n:::: MK ULTRA    -- AN IRIS CROWD FAVORITE & MEMBER OF THE IRIS GIRLS \n\nM.K Ultra is a DJ/ Producer based out of Atlanta playing many genres such as dubstep, house, electro, moombaton, and hardstyle. Known for her high energy and constant movement. She loves producing dubstep and dirty electro. Rising fast as one of the only female dubstep artists in the Atlanta. Playing at your favorite clubs such as Opera, Primal, Luckie Lounge, Connect Lounge, Stoned Studios, QUAD, Spring forth, and other venues she never fails to deliver a high energy dirty set ready to melt your face off and leave you sweating. MK Ultra started DJing in the early summer of 2011 rapidly progressing to be well known in Atlanta for her talent to bring energy to a crowd. She is now booking out of state gigs and is looking at a National summer tour in mid August 2012. Be looking for her new EP soon! MK Ultra claims that this is just what she loves to do. She really genuinely enjoys DJing and is addicted to music production. She can't wait to see how Djing and producing progresses for her in the future. SHE HAS PLAYED WITH HEADLINERS SUCH AS PORTER ROBINSON, AK1200, MARK INSTINCT, MARTY PARTY, HULK, COOKIE MONSTA, POPESKA, OBLIVION, CAPTAIN PANIC, BASSEX, NERD RAGE, DJ MEGAN FOX, DJ COURTNEY, STREET LURKIN, AND MANY MORE! \n\nhey guys! just wanted to drop off my biography and information that you guys can (please) post under my name on the information for the next events whenever i'm playing. \n\nalso, whenever you put my name on the list and flyers, please spell it V3RSATILE, not Versatile. \n\n\n\n \n::::V3RSATILE \n\nV3rsatile is the alter ego of JR Harrison III from Atlanta GA. If you are into the EDM scene at all and have gone to Atlanta Night Clubs (Terminal West, Connect Lounge, Quad, Opera Nightclub, Rush Lounge etc) on any day of the week, chances are you have seen him spin and blend high intensity EDM beats across all genres to the masses. He goes by V3RSATILE because instead of just sticking to one genre of EDM like most other DJ’s, he will spin anything & everything, always heightening the mood and creating unique raging set. Ranging from Progressive & Electro House, Deep Dark Ibiza Tech House, Funky Disco Beats, Trapstep & Oldschool throwbacks, & occasionally some liquid DnB and & Dubstep - Prepare yourself for a musical journey of epic proportions. \n\nV3RSATILE is also the creator and mixer of the Atmospheric Beats Podcasts series, featuring 1-2hr downloadable mixes of epic Progressive House, Funky Disco and Tech House, Trance, Dubstep, & Electro House. Featuring Guests mixes by Wilki-1, Jefferson Deep Balance, Dunsker, and others coming soon. Check out these mixes on soundcloud www.soundcloud.com/atlversatile or mixcloud @ www.mixcloud.com/v3satile . \n\nCome see me every saturday at my Residency at Rush Lounge for the Iris Parties. Stay tuned for the first production EP coming out soon from V3RSATILE, titled Atmospheric Beats \n\nHe has played alongside artists such as DJ Odi, Street Lurkin, James Egbert, Phantom 45, Dirty Talk, Cyberoptics, Hulk, Dara, Numbernin6, Evol Intent, RL Shine, Document One, Nerd Rage, Logistics, DJ Icey, Bad Robots, Eddie Gold, McBeezy, Ployd, Mark Yurm, Arion, AK1200, Danny The Wild Child, Mantis, D.O.H., Lego…. As well as, amongst all other Local EDM ATL DJ’s including Dunsker, MK Ultra, Ployd, Syl-o, Avarice and many others…\n \n \nCheck Out A Mini Documentary on V3RSATILE:\n http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nMPDMI-s5kQ&list=PL4023C44610DFF75E&index=1&feature=plpp_video\n \nwww.facebook.com/atlversatile\nwww.mixcloud.com/v3satile\nwww.soundcloud.com/atlversatile\n\n::::DOUGHBOY\n\nIt all started at midnight on New Years Eve of 1992 in a hole in the wall skating rink. Damien Tucker aka DaddyDough (formerly Doughboy) had been a silent lover of electronic based music for years. When the clock struck 12 his life was changed forever. DaddyDough began his DJ career with old classics, hip hop, and booty shaking tunes. By 1996 Dough had landed regular residencies at several of the hottest electronic clubs in Atlanta. Over the next few years he began to build a strong following, and was playing at several events each week and traveling to some of the hottest venues in the Southeast. Over the last 20 years DaddyDough has played some of the biggest and most talked about venues and events in and around the Atlanta area. A master behind the decks, his smoothness when mixing from tune to tune is rivaled by few in today's scene. Always striving to drop his signature style of Drum and Bass, DaddyDough has remained one of the biggest hidden talents in the Atlanta EDM scene. With the ability to mix any style of dance music and even play track out in the club that even he has never heard sets DaddyDough a step above the nearest competition. DaddyDough is the real deal when he steps behind the decks and not many can say otherwise.\n\nCurrently teamed up with his longtime partner, DJ Quirk, DaddyDough has been making strides to return to the world of production. Under the name EchoLabSoundSystem, Quirk and Dough have been ripping it up in the house realm, while DaddyDough stays true to his roots on solo events, bringing the best in Drum and Bass and his new guilty pleasure, Dubstep. DaddyDough is sure to educate the masses on how it was done back in the day and influence some of the up and coming artists and DJ's on how a true professional works behind the decks to always keep the dance floor moving each time he plays. Aside from his residency and regular Atlanta bookings, you can also always catch DaddyDough each and every Wednesday night from 9pm-12am EST on his internet radio show which has featured some of the biggest local talent from the Atlanta area and beyond. DaddyDough has also shared the stage with some of the biggest and most legendary names in electronic music, including LTJ Bukem, Bad Boy Bill, Simply Jeff, Soul Slinger, 187 aka Jordana, BT, Danny the Wildchild, Keoki, Spacemen, Trip Theory, Frankie Bones, Sandra Collins, and far too many more to name. With all these years mastering his craft, a set by DaddyDough is a sound that is sure not to be missed by anyone who truly calls themselves a lover of electronic dance music.....\n\n::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::\n\n \n::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::\n \nSOUNDCLOUDS & LINKS to some of our Rotational talent:\n \nNEXTaKIN aka D-LEMMA - IRIS, 1200 Hustle\n \nwww.soundcloud.com/nextakin\n \nhttp://www.facebook.com/pages/NextAkin/270309979709197\n \n \n \n\nYOUR OFFICIAL IRIS Masters Of Ceremony for the entire evening:\n \n MC ARION LEE -- http://facebook.com/ArionLeeMC\n \n MC WORD & The Retox Crew w/ Fire Hula Hooper -- http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-MC-WORD-crew/330322437000100\n \n \n \n \n", :start_time => "2012-11-10 22:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-11 05:00:00", :address => "2715 Buford Hwy NE, Atlanta, GA 30324, USA", :fb_id => 414929768534019, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/261175_414929768534019_2132744624_q.jpg", :atenders => 3190, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:32", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:32" },
  { :name => "Imperial Opa Presents: The Masked Charade", :longitude => -84.36389559999999, :latitude => 33.7426397, :gmaps => true, :description => "The Imperial Opa Circus and Rhythma Dance Studios present their Fall production: THE MASKED CHARADE\n\nWHEN:\nNovember 9th 8:30 PM\nNovember 10th 8:30 PM\nNovember 16th 8:30 PM\nNovember 17th (TBA)\n\nWHERE:\nThe Arts Exchange\n750 Kalb Street SE\nAtlanta, GA 30312\n\nFor Tickets: [$20 GA - VIP Tables Available]\nhttp://theimperialopa.com/circus/opa-news/the-masked-charade-ticket-sales?ap_id=littlehoopie\n\nABOUT:\nWhat troubles ensue when we lose our beliefs & don the masks that are not ours?\n\nJoin your local circus for a night of skilled dexterity, ambling fable, and rousing music. \n\nEnjoy AMAZING circus acts that include:\n- Magic\n- Body Stacking\n- Trapeze\n- Spanish Web\n- Break Dancing\n- Hoop Dance\n- Juggling \n- Burlesque\n...and much more!\n\n*Please contact Sarah Cappuccitti with any questions!\n\n \n", :start_time => "2012-11-09 20:30:00", :end_time => "2012-11-17 20:30:00", :address => "798 Kalb St SE, Atlanta, GA 30316, USA", :fb_id => 261082517347103, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc7/373463_261082517347103_1509670745_q.jpg", :atenders => 22, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:37", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:17:37" },
