  { :name => "Faces of Israel: Not Politics.  Not Falafel.  Everything in Between.", :longitude => -82.35020779999999, :latitude => 29.6521776, :gmaps => true, :description => "Just decades ago, David Ben Gurion publicly declared ‘the establishment of a Jewish state… to be known as the State of Israel.’  But what does it mean to be a Jewish state?  Do these two characterizations, ‘democratic state’ and ‘Jewish state’, work well together?  What happens when they don’t?\n\nJoin us at Hillel, Wednesday, November 7th at 5pm where we will dive into the complicated and fascinating aspects of religious identity in Israel with Faces of Israel director Amy Beth Oppenheimer.\n\nFaces of Israel was filmed, edited, and produced by Amy Beth Oppenheimer, a graduate of Johns Hopkins University with a focus on questions surrounding religion and state in Israel. Amy captured interviews with Israelis ranging from openly gay secular university students to leaders in the Masorti movement to Ultra-Orthodox Jews, including Israel’s Ashkenazi Chief Rabbi.\n\nCheck out facesthemovie.com for more info on Amy Beth and the Faces of Israel program!\n\nThis UF Hillel and Jewish Student Union co-sponsored event is open to all students!", :start_time => "2012-11-07 17:30:00", :end_time => "2012-11-07 18:45:00", :address => "Hillel at the University of Florida, Gainesville, FL 32603, USA", :fb_id => 126456264173043, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/276981_126456264173043_996085138_q.jpg", :atenders => 0, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:20:12", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:20:12" },
