  { :name => "Phi Sigma Sigma's 4th Annual Kickball for Kidneys", :longitude => -77.0884181, :latitude => 38.9374776, :gmaps => true, :description => "GRAB LIFE BY THE BALL...\n\n...and join us on Saturday, November 17th on AU campus' turf fields for Phi Sigma Sigma's 4th annual Kickball for Kidneys tournament!\n\nThere will be food, drinks, and AWESOME PRIZES for the winning teams!\n\nAll event proceeds benefit the National Kidney Foundation. For more information visit www.kidney.org.\n\nTeam Registration Information:\n$50 per team, 10 players per team\n\nRegistration/MGC tabling dates:\nThursday, 11/8, 11am-2pm\nFriday, 11/9, 11am-2pm\nMonday, 11/12, 11am-2pm\nTuesday, 11/13, 11am-2pm\nWednesday, 11/14, 11am-2pm\nThursday, 11/15 at 11am-2pm\nFriday, 11/16 at 11am-2pm (QUAD)\n\nIf you have any questions contact:\nOmbeline Picquet op8695a@student.american.edu\nLindsey Patience lindsey.patience@american.edu\n\nSEE YOU ON THE TURF!\n\n", :start_time => "2012-11-17 11:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-17 14:00:00", :address => "3532-3562 Nebraska Ave NW, American University, Washington, DC 20016, USA", :fb_id => 392829717464689, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/203585_392829717464689_1842760881_q.jpg", :atenders => 155, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:08", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:08" },
  { :name => "Students For Liberty Philadelphia Regional Conference", :longitude => -75.1941262, :latitude => 39.9520078, :gmaps => true, :description => "*Registration link:  http://www.surveymonkey.com/s/2012PhiladelphiaRC\n\nJoin Students For Liberty at the University of Pennsylvania on Saturday, November 10 for the 2012 Students For Liberty Philadelphia Regional Conference. We’re excited to return to the University of Pennsylvania this year, site of the first Philadelphia Regional Conference. Since that time the pro-liberty presence in the Philadelphia area has grown exponentially. Students will gather from all over the Northeast for this incredible event.\n\nBy attending the conference, you will hear from top speakers in the libertarian movement, network with other pro-liberty students, discover countless opportunities for jobs, internships, conferences and seminars, and have a lot of fun with other students. This day-long event will feature tremendous speakers, panels, and breakout sessions on the ideas behind a free society and the actions necessary to implement them. In addition, three free meals and drinks at our evening social are included with your FREE registration. Don’t miss out on your chance to be a part of the student movement for liberty! Register today!\n\nFor more information check out the event website here: \nhttp://studentsforliberty.org/event/philadelphia-regional-conference/\n\nKeep in mind attending on facebook DOES NOT guarantee you a spot at the conference. To attend you must register here: http://www.surveymonkey.com/s/2012PhiladelphiaRC", :start_time => "2012-11-10 10:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-10 13:00:00", :address => "Woodland Walk, The Wharton School, University of Pennsylvania, Philadelphia, PA 19104, USA", :fb_id => 180276905437534, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/276725_180276905437534_1459111314_q.jpg", :atenders => 175, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:10", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:10" },
  { :name => "LivingSocial's 5k Dance Party in Washington, D.C.", :longitude => -76.9718671, :latitude => 38.8897318, :gmaps => true, :description => "LivingSocial's 1st glow-in-the-dark 5K Dance Party (http://livingsoci.al/QK67lz) is happening on Friday, Nov. 9 around RFK stadium with an after-party ending inside the Armory. Music will be piped into speakers along the course while people are running so that it creates a moving/running dance party during the run. It's what happens when a 5K meets a dance party. And, we're using a portion of the proceeds to donate solar lamps to schoolchildren in Somalia without electricity to \"light up their night.\"\n\n*Limited tickets available! RSVP here and invite your friends.  The early bird price ($39) is available from now until October 5, and then the price will go up. If you still need a ticket, check out http://livingsoci.al/QK67lz\n\nFor those who are attending the event: Packet pickup will be The Equitable Building at 915 F Street, on Wednesday, 11/7, from 4pm-8pm and Thursday, 11/8, from 4-8pm. Additionally, you can pick-up your packet at the DC Armory (2001 E. Capitol St, DC) on November 9th from 5-6:30pm. However we strongly encourage you to pick up packets on Wednesday or Thursday to alleviate long lines on the race day.\n\n*****Get excited for #5kdanceparty\nFollow the event on Twitter using #5kdanceparty *****\n\nPartners for the 5K Dance Party are d.light and Mercy Corps -- two organizations dedicated to improving the lives of people suffering from the effects of poverty and oppression.", :start_time => "2012-11-09 19:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-09 22:00:00", :address => "201 21st St NE, Washington, DC 20002, USA", :fb_id => 439271472785092, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/276411_439271472785092_1068113426_q.jpg", :atenders => 795, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:12", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:12" },
  { :name => "Queer The Vote - An Election Night Celebration of the LGBTQ Community", :longitude => -77.0267604, :latitude => 38.9971426, :gmaps => true, :description => "Presented by The Ladies of LURe and Zack Rosen Industries\n\nJUST ANNOUNCED: Performers for Queer the Vote\n\nCazwell\nDJ Rosie\nThe Coolots\nLaura Tsagarris\nMichelle Raymond Band\nDJ MIM\n\nStage Sponsor:\nTAGG Magazine - http://www.taggmagazine.com/\n\nIn Partnership with: \n\nThe National Gay and LesbianTask Force - http://thetaskforce.org/\nMixology - Matchmaking with a Twist - http://www.readytomix.com/\nLez Get Together - http://lezgettogether.wix.com/splash\nMarylandGayWeddings.com - http://www.marylandgayweddings.com/\n\nCome together on election night to celebrate the life and times of the LGBTQ community! Bring a sign or make one at the rally table! Enjoy the support of others in the community and find out about initiatives you can be a part of. Put on your dancing shoes and get ready to enjoy a show featuring local LGBTQ artists, singers, comedians, film makers, musicians and more. \n\nTickets On Sale Now at http://bit.ly/TZjMud", :start_time => "2012-11-06 19:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-06 22:00:00", :address => "8661 Colesville Rd, Silver Spring, MD 20910, USA", :fb_id => 109188422573487, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/592217_109188422573487_439300856_q.jpg", :atenders => 101, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:15", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:15" },
  { :name => "PONTIACS EN BAR OPERA CATEDRAL", :longitude => -70.6434525, :latitude => -33.4367116, :gmaps => true, :description => "PONTIACS EN VIVO @ BAR OPERA CATEDRAL\n\nNo se pierdan a Pontiacs presentando sus mejores hits de todos los tiempos, junto a estrenos que formarán parte de su nuevo material, a grabarse a fin de año.\n\nLos esperamos a todos, estará nuestro último disco \"Bursting\" a la venta ($5.000).\n\n23.00 hrs.\nEntrada Liberada\nBar Opera Catedral, José Miguel de la Barra 407, esquina Merced.\n\nhttp://pontiacs.bandcamp.com", :start_time => "2012-11-06 21:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-07 00:00:00", :address => "José Miguel de La Barra 401-499, Santiago, Santiago Metropolitan Region, Chile", :fb_id => 402358436499505, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc7/373467_402358436499505_2012964009_q.jpg", :atenders => 124, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:17", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:17" },
  { :name => "US PRESIDENTIAL ELECTION 2012", :longitude => 2.3030259, :latitude => 48.8601456, :gmaps => true, :description => "Don't miss one of the biggest events of this decade.\nThe coming US Presidential Election will set the pace on all major world issues, from economy to the environment. \nAmerican or not, it concerns us all.\n\nSo, come celebrate with us and watch this broadcast LIVE (in english).\n\nFood and Drink Specials TBA  \n\nThe party will start at 6pm. We'll have music but you'll also get to hear commentaries and perceptions form TV discussions. \nBTW, this is our biggest event ever, so get here early.\n\nThis will be the 57th quadrennial presidential election in which presidential electors, who will officially elect the president and the vice president of the United States on December 17, 2012, will be chosen. Incumbent Democratic President Barack Obama is running for a second and final term during this election. His major challenger is former Massachusetts Governor, Republican Mitt Romney.\n\nYOU MUST BRING YOUR AUP ID \nNon AUP attendants must be accompanied by a student.", :start_time => "2012-11-06 12:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-06 15:00:00", :address => "29 Avenue Bosquet, 75007 Paris, France", :fb_id => 440073989382777, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/203513_440073989382777_1189480534_q.jpg", :atenders => 128, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:19", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:19" },
  { :name => "Masquerade Ball Formal", :longitude => -78.953045, :latitude => 36.0111429, :gmaps => true, :description => "Get ready to have a great time with your friends while looking your best!\n\nThe theme for this year's formal is Masquerade Ball. Dress will be semi-formal to formal, which includes cocktail or formal dresses for ladies and suits for gentlemen. Don't forget your mask! Now is the ideal time to buy one, since stores still have Halloween accessories out.\n\nThe event will be held at the Millennium Hotel in Durham. There will be food and a cash bar at the venue.\n\nMEMP and MEng students are invited to attend.  Tickets will be $5 for an MEMP or MEng student and $10 for guests. Tickets purchased in advance will include a free drink, so keep an eye out for advanced purchase details coming soon!", :start_time => "2012-11-09 20:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-09 23:00:00", :address => "2800 Campus Walk Ave, Durham, NC 27705, USA", :fb_id => 160808617394011, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/188181_160808617394011_1507703977_q.jpg", :atenders => 99, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:21", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:21" },
  { :name => "Destroyed HK presents \"Thursday Tape Delay\" pt.7 at Fly [FREE Entry] Public Event · By Dai Shan 'Destroyed' Na", :longitude => 114.1558424, :latitude => 22.2801874, :gmaps => true, :description => "FREE ENTRY /// NO COVER\n► 9 - 11: Happy Hour\n► 11- late: Dancing\n\nMUSIC:\n► STRICTLY: French Synth Pop // Nu Disco //  Indie-Electro // Disco Funk\n\nDJ SCHEDULE:\n22:00-01:15 // Tête-a-Casque [FRA]\n01:15-04:00 // Celebrity Pool Boy [CAN]\n\nDJs:\n❶ Tête-A-Casque [FRA]\n► He's from France - and he loves to share his music addiction with friends.  What more can you ask for.\n♫ http://soundcloud.com/teteacasque\n\n\n❷ Celebrity Pool Boy [CAN]\n► Listen to new tracks, remixes & mixes @\n♬ http://soundcloud.com/celebrity-pool-boy\n♬ http://www.mixcloud.com/CelebrityPoolBoy/\n\nPHOTOS OF PAST EVENTS\n► Check us out at http://www.facebook.com/getdestroyed/photos", :start_time => "2012-11-08 10:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-08 14:00:00", :address => "2 Lower Albert Rd, Central, Hong Kong", :fb_id => 444696798927941, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/276819_444696798927941_2070916194_q.jpg", :atenders => 17, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:24", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:24" },
  { :name => "Buenos Aires on Broadway Season 3", :longitude => -74.0, :latitude => 40.7166667, :gmaps => true, :description => "Queres estudiar comedia musical en New York? No pudiste venir en agosto pero seguis con ganas de venir! No esperes mas, anotate para nuestra Season 3 de Buenos Aires on Broadway. \n\nLa idea del curso es simple: bueno, barato e intensivo! Sabemos lo costoso que puede ser venir un ano o un semestre entero a NY, por eso creamos un curso unico que incluye dos semanas intensivas de clases con Christopher Stephens y Kathy Morath, asesoría de imagen, canto, repertorio nuevo, técnicas de audición, interpretación, artistas invitados, descuentos para obras y muchas sorpresas mas!\n\nPara mas información, escribir a buenosairesonbroadway@gmail.com\no visita nuestra pagina de internet\nwww.buenosairesonbroadway.com", :start_time => "2013-02-04 22:00:00", :end_time => "2013-02-16 01:00:00", :address => "128-136 White St, New York, NY 10013, USA", :fb_id => 322136961200391, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-prn1/592220_322136961200391_1562171249_q.jpg", :atenders => 24, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:26", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:26" },
  { :name => "2070 UN MUNDO SIN AGUA obra musical de Tatiana Cittadini", :longitude => -58.4070799, :latitude => -34.5992662, :gmaps => true, :description => "2070\nUn mundo sin agua\n\nObra Musical de Tatiana Cittadini\nMúsica original de Marcelo Penco\n\n¡25 artistas en escena!\n\nESTRENO 21 DE NOVIEMBRE\n\n***5 ÚNICAS FUNCIONES***\n\nMiércoles 21 y 28 de noviembre 21:30 hs\nMiércoles 5 de diciembre 19:00 y 21:30 hs\nMiércoles 19 de diciembre 21:30 hs\n\nTeatro El Cubo, Zelaya 3053\nO través de www.alternativateatral.com\nEntradas $90\nDuración del espectáculo: 90 min.\n\nElenco:\nJuano Mansilla, Martín Gentile, Estefanía Von Petery, Jonathan Bromberg, Ivan Asborno, \nJorge Bar, Carolina López, Rodrigo Carbajal, Julieta Sibilia, Alba Almirón, Emilse Soriano, \nNicolás Ayardi, Facundo Massuco, Federico Araujo, María Espina, Sofia Larriera, \nXimena Pintos, Menelik Cambiaso, Victoria Caballero, Jonatan Fells, Lara Lorenzo, \nMaría Belén Calabrese, Sara De Petre\n\nLetras de canciones: Nicolás Ayardi y Tatiana Cittadini\nLibro: Nicolás Ayardi y Tatiana Cittadini\nMúsica original: Marcelo Penco\nArreglos vocales y Dirección vocal: Gaby Giangrante\nCoreografías: Tatiana Cittadini \nEquipo creativo: Juano Mansilla, Nicolás Ayardi y Tatiana Cittadini\nEscenografía: Natalia Castez, María Emilia Marozzi, Agustina Montemurri y Equipo creativo Artes Opuestos\nMaquillaje: Sol Ferrero, Lucila Abramian, Natalia Castez y Mariel Magallanes\nVestuario: Rocío Luz Alvarez\nProducción ejecutiva: Equipo creativo Artes Opuestos\nFotografía: Ivan Asborno\nGráfica: Equipo creativo Artes Opuestos\nPrensa: Ayni Comunicación\nIdea original: Tatiana Cittadini\nDirección General: Tatiana Cittadini\n\n2070 Un mundo sin agua cuenta la historia de un futuro destruido ambiental y socialmente. Un grupo de científicos tiene en sus manos el poder de decidir lo que sucederá con la población para que no continúen las muertes por falta de alimentos, agua y una calidad de vida muy baja, poniendo en marcha investigaciones en las que trabajaron durante años.\nEstos científicos llevan a cabo el plan AO-2070 que trata de convertir a las personas en androides para limpiar la raza y poder salvar el 60% de la población. Para esto, crean un reducto en el cual las personas son llevadas para ser tratadas y poner en marcha su investigación.\n\nWeb: www.artesopuestos.com.ar\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/2070UnMundoSinAgua\nTwitter: @ArtesOpuestos\n\nEsta obra formó parte del festival CTM 2012", :start_time => "2012-11-21 19:30:00", :end_time => "2012-12-19 19:30:00", :address => "Jean Jaures 902-1000, Buenos Aires, Autonomous City of Buenos Aires, Argentina", :fb_id => 116201011869143, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/203532_116201011869143_861700803_q.jpg", :atenders => 137, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:29", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:22:29" },
