  { :name => "HLCF presents: SALSAthon!", :longitude => -82.34891879999999, :latitude => 29.6502481, :gmaps => true, :description => "When? Wednesday, November 7 \nTime? 7pm-10pm\nDoors open at 6pm\nSalsa STARTS at 7pm until 10pm\n\nWhere? Rion Ballroom\n\n Proceeds donated to Children Beyond Our Borders, Inc. \n\nDancer Registration will open soon!\n$5 per person per couple. \n$7 individual\n$10 at the door. \n\nTHE 2013 HISPANIC-LATINO COLLEGIATE FORUM\nHispanic Latino Collegiate Forum is three-day conference consists of a variety of workshops that range from professional development to advocating for Latino rights.\n\nPlease visit our FB Page:\nhttps://www.facebook.com/HLCF.UF\n\nThere will be keynote speakers, leadership training, network opportunities, and merit awards given. \n\nWe expect approximately 200 participants to be present at this forum that consist of exceptional Hispanic-Latino student leaders in the state of Florida. At this forum, students will have the opportunity to learn about issues that affect the Latino community. As well as, gain valuable information and develop skills on how to bring change at their respective institutions and community.\n\nThis year, the forum will be held on March 22nd-24th, 2013. During the time leading up to the forum the HLCF team will be putting on different events, fundraisers, and activities. \n\nOur first big event is SALSAthon which we would like to formally invite you to join! \n\n\nGamma Eta Sorority, Inc.\nHispanic Student Association\nChildren Beyond Our Borders\nGator Salsa Club\nPorColombia\n\nGator Salsa Club will be teaching salsa from 6-7pm\nGina Castano will lead us into the night...\nMore instructors coming soon!\n\n\nPlease fill out this survey if your organization would like to Co-Sponsor SALSAthon!\nhttps://docs.google.com/a/chbob.org/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dGlOcUl0ODFBOFJFTmExZHVjVTRRdEE6MQ#gid=0 ", :start_time => "2012-11-07 18:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-07 22:00:00", :address => "1578-1652 Gale Lemerand Dr, Gainesville, FL 32608, USA", :fb_id => 497690406922763, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/276554_497690406922763_1758727073_q.jpg", :atenders => 76, :privacy => nil, :created_at => "2012-11-05 22:27:15", :updated_at => "2012-11-05 22:27:15" },
  { :name => "Havana Cultura 2012", :longitude => -70.62782500000002, :latitude => -33.4302804, :gmaps => true, :description => "Havana Club te invita a ser parte nuestro festival Havana Cultura, este 9 y 10 de noviembre en el Centro Cultural Montecarmelo.\n\nPara conseguir tu entrada GRATIS, debes participar ingresando La Aduana: http://bit.ly/miradasHC \n\nResponde las preguntas y luego quédate atento a tu correo asociado a Facebook. Así de fácil.\n\nHavana Cultura trae Cuba hasta el corazón de Santiago a artistas visuales, músicos, percusionistas, quienes llenarán de color el barrio Bellavista.\n \nMúsica en vivo, instalaciones y djs se complementarán con puestos de serigrafías, carritos de granizados, graffitis, autos antiguos, bicicletas cubanas y los tradicionales jugadores de Dominó. Una fiesta ambientada como en la Habana Vieja y animada con la música del grupo Sandonga.\n \nA los amantes del ron les daremos a conocer los secretos de sus preparaciones gracias a la recreación de los míticos bares “El Floridita” y  “La Bodeguita del Medio” conocidos por realizar los mejores mojitos y daikiris del mundo, junto a muchas sorpresas más. \n\nRecuerda que para obtener tu entrada: \n1. Ingresa a nuestra TAB http://bit.ly/miradasHC \n2. Participa en la sección la Aduana haciendo click en \"tomar test\". \n3. Responde las preguntas. Sin ser necesario que todas sean correctas, serás parte del sorteo de las entradas que enviaremos al email de tu cuenta de Facebook.\n\n¡Participa y sé parte de Havana Cultura! \n\nRevisa lo que será nuestro festival: http://bit.ly/QUx1dt\n\nRecuerda beber con moderación. \n \n\n", :start_time => "2012-11-09 20:00:00", :end_time => "2012-11-09 23:00:00", :address => "Monte Carmelo 2-26, Providencia, Santiago Metropolitan Region, Chile", :fb_id => 165665753573412, :owner_id => nil, :city => nil, :country => nil, :picture => "https://fbcdn-profile-a.akamaihd.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/188174_165665753573412_173049800_q.jpg", :atenders => 183, :priv